The ANC's Gwede Mantashe is due to explain the formal programme for the policy conference after it was adopted by the national executive committee on Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG African National Congress (ANC) secretary-general Gwede Mantashe is due to publicly announce the formal programme for the party's policy conference on Thursday.Delegates will meet from Friday until Wednesday to discuss the party s policy proposals amid demands for radical economic change and an end to what some in the party call white monopoly capital.Mantashe is due to explain the formal programme for the policy conference after it was adopted by the ANC s national executive committee on Wednesday.Delegates will spend most of the gathering in commissions, discussing issues like economic transformation, organisational renewal and peace and security.But this conference will also be a test of strength between those who support deputy president Cyril Ramaphosa and Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma.A key moment may come when President Jacob Zuma formally opens the conference and delegates see both him and Ramaphosa.WATCH: ANC policy conference: What's at stake?Meanwhile, ANC stalwarts are expected to shed more light on plans not to attend the party s policy conference which starts on Friday.The veterans have called on President Jacob Zuma to step down as well as all those implicated in the state of capture report.The stalwarts had asked for a special stand-alone conference in the first two days of the ANC s policy meeting which appears to have fallen on deaf ears.